                                Test Plan for EasyEMR Application 


                 |--- Admin Page ---|



Admin Test 1 
------


Admin user should login as admin and be redirected to admin page.
Admin user should click button to list all users.  
Admin user should then select a user and modify each of the following user fields:
    
    1) First name
    
    2) Last  name
    
    3) user name
    
    4) password
    
    5) role
    

Admin user should then save user information.
Admin user should then go back and click list users.
Admin user should click on the same name.
User information should reflect changes.


Admin Test 2
------


Admin user should login with admin credentials
Admin user should be redirected to admin page.
Admin user should enter in user information for new user account
Admin user should submit user account to be saved
Admin user should go back and list all users
New user should be listed.



                 |--- Triage Page ---|



Triage Test 1
------


Nurse/Student should login with credentials
User should be redirected to triage page.
User should enter in first and last name of patient
If name shows in patient history user should select the patient to fill the data. 
User should fill in additional patient information and click submit.


Triage Test 2
------


User should enter in all fields except required fields and hit submit.
if application functions properly patient information should not have be submitted to database


Triage Test 3
------


Data validation - User should enter wrong data fields in the input box and click submit.



                 |--- Medical Page ---|
                 


When Patient ID is searched, only one user should be displayed in the table (consider filling information automatically for patient ID search).

when patient first name and last name is searched, there are several possible outcomes.  Each are listed below:

   1) If multiple patients exist in the database when first or last name is searched, all matching patients will be displayed
   
   2) If only one patient matching the search criteria exist in the database one patient will be displayed.
    
    
Medical Test 1
--------------


User should type in the following information in the search fields separtely and click the search button:
    
    1) Patient ID
    
    2) First Name
    
    3) Last Name



Medical Test 2
--------------


Medical Test 2
--------------


                 |--- Pharmacy Page ---|
                 

                 
Upon logging in, all prescribed selection boxes should be defaulted to yes.

If the user selects no, a input box to type in prescribed medication should render.

As the user types in medication a list of medications beginning with input text should display.



Pharmacy Test 1
---------------


User should type in the following information in the search fields separtely and click the search button:
    
    1) Patient ID
    
    2) First Name
    
    3) Last Name


Once a patient is displayed int eh search display table, user should select patient.  Previous information on patient regarding problem list and medication given should be displayed.  
User should select a patient that has been given the medication that was prescribed.  All selection boxes should have "yes" selected.
User should select a patient that has been not been given the medication that was prescribed.  All selection boxes should have "no" selected.
User should select a patient that has a mix of medication that is same as prescribed and different than prescribed.  Selection boxes should have "yes" / "no" corresponding to patient data.

User should submit information each time.  Data in database should reflect changes in each session.



